external_knowledge:
- A positive average price indicates that the category has at least one product with a price greater than zero;
- The `LEFT JOIN` operation ensures that all categories are included, even if they have no sub-categories or products;
- The `GROUP BY` clause is used to aggregate the data by category name.

sql:
SELECT COUNT(*) 
FROM cart_items 
WHERE product_id = 1 AND user_id = 1 AND item_final_price = 1199.0;

external_knowledge:
- 'expensive items' refers to products with a price greater than $3000;
- 'the last month' refers to October 2023;
- 'sum of the final item prices' includes discounts applied to the items.

- 'blossoms' refers to products;
- 'gardeners' refers to customers;
- 'gained recognition' refers to high sales (quantity sold > 50);
- 'earned the admiration' refers to high ratings (average rating);
- 'plucked' refers to the quantity sold.

- "glowing reviews" refers to ratings greater than 4;
- "dim reviews" refers to ratings less than 4;
- "average radiance of their praise" refers to the average rating of the product.

- "garned more than 100 views" refers to products that have been viewed more than 100 times;
- "over 50 orders" refers to products that have been ordered more than 50 times;
- "stars that have attracted both many gazes and admirers" is a metaphor for popular products that have both high visibility and high sales.

- "Blossoms" refers to products;
- "Praised" refers to having a high average rating (greater than 4.0);
- "Petals" refers to product variations;
- "Top 3 petals by stock quantity" refers to the top 3 variations of each product ranked by stock quantity.

- "stars of the show" refers to products with the highest total revenue;
- "shining bright" emphasizes the prominence of these products in terms of revenue;
- "realm of customer ratings" refers to the average rating of the products.

- "Garden" refers to the product categories;
- "Flowers" or "Blossoms" refer to the products;
- "Blossoms" also symbolize the product count;
- "Average value of blossoms" refers to the average price of the products;
- "Sub-garden" refers to the sub-categories.

- "vast garden of products" refers to the collection of all products across different categories and sub-categories;
- "boast the crowns" refers to the top-ranked products based on average ratings;
- "highest-rated titles" refers to the products with the highest average rating in each sub-category.

- 'High rating' refers to a rating value of 4 or above;
- 'First view' indicates the initial time a user viewed a product;
- 'Most viewed' means the products are ordered by the number of views they have received.

- 'Last year' refers to the year 2022;
- 'Most recent three orders' are determined by the order dates in descending order;
- 'User' refers to the user with `user_id = 0`.

- "Average view duration" is the mean duration of views for products in a category;
- "Top 3 categories" refers to the categories with the highest average view durations;
- "Most viewed product" is the product with the highest number of views within its category.

- 'Good ratings' are defined as ratings with a value of 4 or higher out of 5;
- 'Total views' include both desktop and mobile views;
- 'Rating rank' is determined by the number of good ratings, with higher numbers of good ratings receiving a lower rank number.

- Search queries with the intent to buy are considered;
- The most recent search query before the order is used for analysis;
- The highest-ranked order (i.e., the order with the highest total value) for each user is selected;
- The total sales are calculated by summing the total value of the items in the highest-ranked orders.

- "captured the attention" implies that the user spent more than 30 seconds viewing the product;
- "brief glance" refers to a view duration less than or equal to 30 seconds;
- "viewed more than once" indicates that the product has been viewed by at least two different view events.

- "Most versatile" refers to the product that is popular across multiple sub-categories;
- "Top 3 most ordered" means the products with the highest quantity ordered in each sub-category;
- "Average rating of 4 or higher" indicates products that are well-received by customers.
